    <note>Song(2) Bangguang [10969] Fujian TZ, 148.2a. A man of exactly this name married the 4th daughter (second, who survived to marriage) of Zhao(1) Huizong [9008] in 1117 and became the father-in-law of Zhao(1) Bogui [17676], Zhao(1) Xiaozong's [9011] elder brother. He holds a military office in the notice in HSSCGY, 15.4a, but this would have been automatic upon marriage with an imperial princess. His entry in the Fujian TZ jinshi lists notes his highest office as Prefect of Lianshui jun, which existed between 1085 and 1135. The chronology is correct and given the ancestral home of Cai(1) Jing [1649], the linkage with Putian is not unusual, after all one of Cai(1) Jing's sons was married to a daughter of Huizong.</note>
